    /**
     * Creates a {@link MemoryRecordsBuilder} for constructing a new batch using the current magic
     * version, the given compression and timestamp type, starting at {@code baseOffset}, and
     * capped at {@code maxSize} bytes.
     *
     * <p>When the timestamp type is {@link TimestampType#LOG_APPEND_TIME}, the log-append
     * timestamp is set to the current wall-clock time at the moment this method is called.
     *
     * @param buffer        the buffer to write the encoded batch into; must not be {@code null}
     * @param compression   the compression codec to apply to record data
     * @param timestampType the timestamp type
     * @param baseOffset    the base offset of the first record in the batch
