                producerId, producerEpoch, baseSequence, partitionLeaderEpoch, records);
    }

    /**
     * Builds a {@link MemoryRecords} containing the given {@link SimpleRecord} objects using the
     * specified magic version, initial offset, compression, and timestamp type. No idempotent or
     * transactional metadata is embedded.
     *
     * @param magic         the record format magic byte
     * @param initialOffset the base offset to assign to the first record
     * @param compression   the compression codec to apply
     * @param timestampType the timestamp type
     * @param records       the records to include; varargs
     * @return an immutable {@link MemoryRecords} containing the serialised batch
     */
    public static MemoryRecords withRecords(byte magic, long initialOffset, Compression compression,
                                            TimestampType timestampType, SimpleRecord... records) {
        return withRecords(magic, initialOffset, compression, timestampType, RecordBatch.NO_PRODUCER_ID,
                RecordBatch.NO_PRODUCER_EPOCH, RecordBatch.NO_SEQUENCE, RecordBatch.NO_PARTITION_LEADER_EPOCH,
                false, records);
    }

    /**
     * Builds a {@link MemoryRecords} containing the given {@link SimpleRecord} objects with full
     * control over all batch header fields. This is the most general {@code withRecords} overload;
     * all other overloads delegate to this method.
     *
     * <p><b>Performance note:</b> The method estimates the required buffer size upfront based on
     * {@link AbstractRecords#estimateSizeInBytes} and uses a resizable
     * {@link ByteBufferOutputStream} to handle cases where the estimate is too small. Only a
     * single batch is created per call.
     *
     * @param magic                the record format magic byte
     * @param initialOffset        the base offset to assign to the first record
     * @param compression          the compression codec to apply
     * @param timestampType        the timestamp type
     * @param producerId           the idempotent/transactional producer id, or
     *                             {@link RecordBatch#NO_PRODUCER_ID}
     * @param producerEpoch        the producer epoch, or {@link RecordBatch#NO_PRODUCER_EPOCH}
     * @param baseSequence         the base sequence number, or {@link RecordBatch#NO_SEQUENCE}
     * @param partitionLeaderEpoch the partition leader epoch
     * @param isTransactional      {@code true} if the batch belongs to a transaction
     * @param records              the records to include; varargs
     * @return an immutable {@link MemoryRecords} containing the serialised batch, or
     *         {@link #EMPTY} if {@code records} is empty
     */
    public static MemoryRecords withRecords(byte magic, long initialOffset, Compression compression,
                                            TimestampType timestampType, long producerId, short producerEpoch,
                                            int baseSequence, int partitionLeaderEpoch, boolean isTransactional,
                                            SimpleRecord... records) {
        if (records.length == 0)
            return MemoryRecords.EMPTY;
        int sizeEstimate = AbstractRecords.estimateSizeInBytes(magic, compression.type(), Arrays.asList(records));
        ByteBufferOutputStream bufferStream = new ByteBufferOutputStream(sizeEstimate);
        long logAppendTime = RecordBatch.NO_TIMESTAMP;
        if (timestampType == TimestampType.LOG_APPEND_TIME)
            logAppendTime = System.currentTimeMillis();
        try (final MemoryRecordsBuilder builder = new MemoryRecordsBuilder(bufferStream, magic, compression, timestampType,
                initialOffset, logAppendTime, producerId, producerEpoch, baseSequence, isTransactional, false,
                partitionLeaderEpoch, sizeEstimate)) {
            for (SimpleRecord record : records)
                builder.append(record);
            return builder.build();
        }
